    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>A moment ago you knew everything. Now you know nothing. Not even where you are. Not even *who* you are. 

Your heel is raising from the shattered remains of a device you just stomped on, but you can't remember why you stomped on it. People whose faces you should recall are shouting at you, terrified and enraged, but you don't know their names. 

An older man shoves you. "Gurian, you lunatic! What have you done?"

"He's stranded us!" says a middle aged woman. "Now we can't get back!"

"And where are we?" asks a younger woman. 

"We are still in Archopalasia," says a younger man, turning in a circle. "In fact the very same room we left from. The real question is, *when* are we?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
