    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>The older man laughs. "That's your best play? Please, Gurian. How many years have we worked with you? You have the sharpest memory of all of us. If you think I'm going to believe you conveniently--"

"Wait, Dorden," says the middle aged woman. "He may be telling the truth. You know I've had my suspicions before about our mysterious colleague. Let me just..."

Dorden rolls his eyes as she rummages in her bag. "Not this again, Paelus. You see our nemesis in everything."

"And why shouldn't I, when our sole purpose is to rob him?" Paelus takes out a flat glass pentagon and peers at you through it, then groans. "His spectrum is entirely changed. It *was* him. Gurian was the Changing God."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>The older man laughs. "You don't, eh? Well there's four of us and one of you, so..."

"Wait, Dorden," says the middle aged woman. She peers intently at you. "There's something different about him. Let me just..." She rummages in her bag and pulls out a flat glass pentagon.

Dorden rolls his eyes. "Not this again, Paelus."

"Humor me," she says. "You know I've had my suspicions before about our mysterious colleague." 

"You see our nemesis in everything," says Dorden.

"And why shouldn't I, when our sole purpose is to rob him?" Paelus peers at you through the glass, then groans. "His spectrum is entirely changed. It *was* him. Gurian was the Changing God."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Catch him!" shouts the older man. 

Fenne tackles you from behind, then rolls you over as the others surround you. 

The old man glares. "Answer the question."

"Wait, Dorden," The middle aged woman, peers at you. "There's something different about him. Let me..." She pulls a flat glass pentagon from her bag.

Dorden rolls his eyes. "Not this again, Paelus."

"Humor me," she says. "You know I've had my suspicions about our mysterious colleague." 

"You see our nemesis in everything," Dorden growls.

"Why shouldn't I, when we're out to rob him?" Paelus peers at you through the glass, then groans. "His spectrum is entirely changed. It *was* him. Gurian was the Changing God."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well, I'm not dying here," growls Dorden. "There were other void spheres in our Archopalasia. Perhaps some survived. We'll search for them, then we'll go back and take our revenge."

"And who will pilot the sphere?" asked Fenne. "Only Gurian knew the interface. Does he now?"

The four of them turn to you, questioning. "Well," says Dorden. "Do you?"

You look down at the broken device at your feet and strain to recall it's use. Sensations come to you - your fingers manipulating the rings, your thumb pressing a button. It seems your hands remember more than your mind does.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
