    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>The older man stares around. The room looks like a workshop, with walls of synth and glass and tables littered with tools and machines, but its all ruined. Everything is weathered and cracked and covered in dust, and half the windows are missing, letting in a frigid wind that cuts through your light robes. "You're right, Fenne," he says. "We haven't moved an inch, but--"

The older woman gasps and hurries to the broken glass. "The plains! They're gone! It's a desert!"

The others join her, looking down at endless brown wastes, far below. "I predicted this," says Fenne. "We're in Archopalasia's future, after it's killed itself. And soon it'll kill us too."</DefaultText>
