    <Entry>
      <ID>116</ID>
      <DefaultText>The young woman turns to you, tears in her eyes. "Why, Gurian? Why have you done this? You've killed yourself as surely as you've killed us."

"Aye," says the older man. "We were so close to immortality we could taste it, and now... unless by some miracle we find food and water and warm clothing in this hell, we'll all be dead within a day. Why did you do it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>117</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Was?" asks the younger woman. "And what is he now?"

"A husk, Elia," says Paelus. "Nothing but a husk. The Changing God used this body to infiltrate us, steal our science, and learn if we were a threat to him. And when he determined we were, he tricked us into following him to this time, crushed the only means of returning to our own, then fled to another body, leaving this empty vessal to face our wrath."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
