    <Entry>
      <ID>121</ID>
      <DefaultText>They eye you uncertainly. 

"I'm not sure I'm encouraged by the swiftness of your answer," says Dorden. "Don't forget, your survival depends on this as much as ours does. If you can't do it, we all die here, and soon."

He turns for the door, motioning for you and the others to follow. "Now come on, this is all moot if we can't find another void disk and piloting egg. Turn on your voxes and let's search."

It is only as the others touch them that you notice that they all have clear disks stuck on their cheekbones near their ears. You touch your own cheek and find you have one too. As you touch it, you can hear all their voices in your ear.</DefaultText>
