      <DefaultText>They eye you uneasily. 

"Well, at least you're honest," says Dorden. "Don't forget, your survival depends on this as much as ours does. If you can't remember, we all die here, and soon."

He turns for the door, motioning for you and the others to follow. "Now come on, this is all moot if we can't find another void disk and piloting egg. Let's search."</DefaultText>
